<paragraph id="8BD336B3FFF0F941FF3BFA22646EF946" blockId="52.[151,1437,1474,1967]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFF0F941FF3BFA2267E8FA12" bold="true" box="[151,413,1474,1499]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Elevated limpet-shaped shell; oval basal outline; recurved apex reaching the posterior margin; anal slit deep and adapically rounded; selenizone bordered by raised flanges; strong radial ribs gradually increasing in number by intercalation; weaker concentric ribs in the interspaces between the radials. Protoconch: planispiral, slightly turned to the right; slightly less than 1.25 whorls; diameter about 150 µm; flocculent to reticulated micro-ornament on early part of protoconch, later arranged roughly in collabral rows; transition to the teleoconch marked by a low varix.
</paragraph>
